The paper proposes a new approach for multi-label classification that involves embedding the label network and using it to extend input space in learning and inference of any base multi-label classifier. This approach involves machine learning techniques and is focused on improving the performance of multi-label classification. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). Other likely sub-categories include cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CV (Computer Vision), cs.CL (Computation and Language), and cs.IR (Information Retrieval), as these sub-categories are also related to machine learning and classification tasks.
